description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a confident Band 7 Occupational Therapist who would like to explore a more rewarding clinical challenge in one of our personality disorder services? Are you ready to develop your clinical skills further in a supportive team? We want to recruit an exceptional OT to our Band 7 post. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Would you like to further your career with us?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cygnet Acer Clinic is a 28 bed rehabilitation service providing assessment, treatment and rehabilitation for women with personality disorder and complex needs. Rehabilitation is provided in a therapeutic environment, with a level of security matched to individual needs. The aim of the treatment, rehabilitation and re-socialisation programme is to prepare the people in our care either for transfer to conditions of lesser security, or for a life in the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post:&lt;/strong&gt;(Band 7) Highly Specialist Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base:&lt;/strong&gt;Cygnet Acer Clinic&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Caseload:&lt;/strong&gt; 28 patients (Split between the post holder and the band 6 in post)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsible for:&lt;/strong&gt;The post holder will line manage and lead a Band 6 OT &amp; an Activity Coordinators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsible to:&lt;/strong&gt;Service Manager for Line management supervision &amp; Occupational Therapist (Band 8 or above) for professional supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours:&lt;/strong&gt;32 hours per week (4 days a week)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;Acer Clinic, Worksop Rd, Mastin Moor, Chesterfield S43 3DN&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our supportive friendly team and make an application today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With over 150 OTs in the company, we also work together as a large team providing support to each other across the group, with various specialist interest groups to tap into, including Mental Health, Neuropsychiatry, Autism, Learning Disabilities and Sensory Integration, to name a few.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Occupational Therapist, you will provide direct clinical care which will encompass OT assessments, treatment and management of patients within the service.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; In this role you will assess, implement and develop an OT treatment programme according to our patient’s diagnosis and identified needs. This will be based upon findings from assessments including associated risks, in order to develop treatment plans accordingly.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Prioritisation skills are key to manage the caseload of clients effectively and you will work closely with the Occupational Therapy and multidisciplinary team onsite.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5 reasons why you should make an application today…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We care about people in our services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Career pathway progression within the company to support your development and skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will be part of a team providing excellent care to our patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;National networks of over 150 OTs in the Cygnet Group within different specialisms including Forensic Practice, LD and ASD, Acute mental health, PICU, and inpatient CAMHS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Low caseload of 28 (with the addition of a band 6 OT) to support intensive OT focused interventions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Successful Candidate should be/have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A registered Occupational Therapist with the HCPC (Health Care Professions Council)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in the field of personality disorder&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working as a Band 6 or Band 7 OT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding of Occupational Therapy process/interventions and can take a “hands on” approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and time management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage highly demanding clinical presentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In return we will offer you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A competitive salary of up to £40,000pa FTE DoE&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for CPD and to undertake further learning and development. For example: Leadership and Management, Sensory Integration.&lt;br /&gt; Training days provided by highly experienced and renowned OT specialists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert clinical supervision and peer support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bi-monthly OT CPD meetings focused on skill and strategic service development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Discount Cards &amp; Blue Light Card&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free parking &amp; meals on duty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relocation packages offered&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; The successful candidate will be required to undergo an enhanced DBS and reference check and an offer of employment will be subject to successful clearance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*Please note - speculative recruitment emails are not to be sent directly to our clinical staff, these need to go via our internal recruitment team. If speculative candidates are sent directly to a member of the clinical team, we will consider these candidates as our own*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What next?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you care about making a difference – we want to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion about the role please our dedicated Occupational Therapy in-house recruiter Hayleyvalentine@cygnethealth.co.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click the link to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
